column1: Percentage value is a comparison of emissions in target year vs. actual 2005 emissions for developed countries, which includes the US, European Union, Norway and Sweden, Russia and the former republics of the Soviet Union and the former Yugoslavia, Japan, Canada, South Korea, Australia and New Zealand, and Albania.

Percentage value is a comparison of emissions in target year vs. actual 2005 emissions for rapidly developing countries, which includes many of the fastest developing and larger nations: China, India, Brazil, South Africa, Mexico, Indonesia, the Philippines, Thailand, Taiwan, Hong Kong, Malaysia, Pakistan and Singapore.
Percentage value is a comparison of emissions in target year vs. actual 2005 emissions for other developing countries.
